#Text=Search and Find About Someone Using Image
#Text=Easily
#Text=Have a picture of someone , but do n't know who it is , or what the picture means ?
#Text=You can use various image searching tools online to find other copies of the image , track down the origin , and discover more information .
#Text=Google Images and TinEye are the most popular options , and you can even do it from your mobile device .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Using Google Image Search
#Text=Find the image that you want to search with .
#Text=You can use Google to search by image instead of text .
#Text=Google will attempt to find other copies of the same image on the internet , as well as provide visually similar images .
#Text=This can help you determine where the picture originated from , and potentially find more pictures of the same person .
#Text=You can search from images that have been saved to your computer , or you can search using the image 's URL .
#Text=To find an image 's address , right-click on it and select " Copy image address/URL . "
#Text=To save an image to your computer , right-click on it and select " Save image . "
#Text=If you 're using a mobile device , click here instead .
#Text=Visit the Google Images website .
#Text=Visit in your browser .
#Text=You 'll see the familiar Google search field .
#Text=Click the Camera button on the right side of the search field .
#Text=This will allow you to search by image .
#Text=Add your image that you want to search with .
#Text=There are two ways to search by image :
#Text=Select " Paste image URL " and paste the copied address into the field .

column1: #Text=Select " Upload an image " and browse for the image that you saved to your computer .
#Text=Click " Search by image . "
#Text=A list of search results will be displayed .
#Text=If the image was found in other sizes , these will be displayed at the top .
#Text=Pages where the same image can be found will be displayed beneath , and visually similar images can be found at the bottom of the first page of results .
#Text=Using TinEye
#Text=Find the image that you want to search with .
#Text=TinEye is a search engine designed to search through images .
#Text=You can search using either an image 's URL or by uploading an image file .
#Text=While TinEye does not find similar images , you can use it to quickly trace the origin of an image .
#Text=To find an image 's address , right-click on it and select " Copy image address/URL . "
#Text=To save an image to your computer , right-click on it and select " Save image . "
#Text=Visit the TinEye website .
#Text=Go to in your web browser .
#Text=Upload your image or paste your copied URL .
#Text=Click the Upload button to browse your computer for an image file , or paste the copied image URL into the field .
#Text=Browse through the search results .
#Text=TinyEye will only return results for the same image , so browse through the results to find the origin of the image file .
#Text=Visit pages with the image to potentially find more information .
#Text=The page that contains the image may be able to give you more information as to the person 's identity .
#Text=Check out a couple of the results to see if you can learn more about the person in the image .
#Text=Look for image captions or the paragraph text around the image .
#Text=Using a Mobile Device
#Text=Install the Chrome browser for your device .
#Text=You ca n't use the Google Image Search website to search by image on a mobile device , but you can use the Chrome mobile browser to search instead .
#Text=You can get Chrome for free from your device 's app store if you do n't have it already .
#Text=This method works for both iOS and Android .
#Text=You can also use TinEye ( above ) by copying and pasting the URL for the image that you want to search with .
#Text=Press and hold an image and select " Copy image address " to copy the URL to your device 's clipboard .
#Text=You can then paste this into the TinEye search field .
#Text=Find the picture you want to search with .
#Text=You ca n't upload an image , but you can search using any picture you come across online .
#Text=Use Chrome to navigate to the image that you want to search with .
#Text=If you only have an image file on your computer , upload it to an image host like Imgur first and then navigate to it on your mobile device .
#Text=Press and hold on the image that you want to search with .
#Text=A menu will appear after a moment .
#Text=Select " Search Google for this image . "
#Text=This will perform a Google Image search based off the image you pressed .
#Text=Browse through the results .
#Text=Google will provide its best guess for what the image name is , as well as provide links to pages that its used on .
#Text=Visually similar images can be found at the bottom of the first page of results .
#Text=Video
#Text=Tips
#Text=TinEye is great for checking to see if someone who is claiming an image is an original image of them actually is !
#Text=Put in the image details of anyone you know on line , even wikiHow profile pictures , and see how many other times ' their picture ' has been used on line .
#Text=Quick Summary
